---
layout: layouts/default.njk
title: Trading Page
---

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row align-items-center">

    <!-- Left Side: Screenshot Carousel -->
    <div class="col-lg-6 pe-lg-7">
      <div class="image-container">
        <div id="screenshotCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
          <div class="carousel-inner">
            <!-- First image -->
            <div class="carousel-item active">
              <img src="/src/image/pnl_graph.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Trading Bot Screenshot 1">
            </div>
            <!-- Second image -->
            <div class="carousel-item">
              <img src="/src/image/performance_data.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Trading Bot Screenshot 2">
            </div>
            
          </div>

          <!-- Carousel arrows -->
          <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#screenshotCarousel" data-bs-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
          </button>
          <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#screenshotCarousel" data-bs-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right Side: Text -->
    <div class="col-lg-6">
      <div class="text-container text-light">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Open Range Breakout Bot / Backtester</h2>
        <p>
          This desktop software is designed to backtest futures markets and execute trades in real time. 
          It was built using NinjaScript, a C#-based language specifically for trading that runs on the .NET framework. 
          Users can run historical backtests on any futures market to evaluate performance, 
          or attach the strategy to a live chart and configure parameters such as the number of contracts, 
          profit targets, and stop losses.
        </p>

        <h5 class="mt-4">Technologies used</h5>
        <ul>
          <li>C#</li>
          <li>NinjaTrader 8</li>
          <li>.NET Framework</li>
          <li>NinjaTrader API (Cbi, Data, NinjaScript, Gui.Tools)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
